On Purple Heart Day, the President and First Lady honor the soldiers who have received the Purple Heart for their immense suffering and sacrifice in service to the nation. The Purple Heart was established by General George Washington 237 years ago and was later revived by General Douglas MacArthur. It is a symbol of heroism and the price of the nation's liberty and peace. The President and First Lady express gratitude to all Purple Heart recipients, their families, and Gold Star Families for their sacrifice and devotion to duty.